SPECIMEN FROM ORGANISM ID (Required): A unique ID for the biomaterial.
SPECIMEN FROM ORGANISM NAME: A short, descriptive name for the biomaterial that need not be unique.
SPECIMEN FROM ORGANISM DESCRIPTION: A general description of the biomaterial.
GENUS SPECIES (Required): The scientific binomial name for the species of the specimen.
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
ORGAN (Required): A term that may be associated with an anatomy-related ontology term.
ORGAN ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
ORGAN ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
ORGAN PART: A term for a specific part of the organ that the biomaterial came from.
ORGAN PART ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
ORGAN PART ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
KNOWN DISEASE(S): Short description of known disease(s) of the specimen.
KNOWN DISEASE(S) ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
KNOWN DISEASE(S) ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
INPUT DONOR ORGANISM ID (Required): A unique ID for the biomaterial.
COLLECTION PROTOCOL ID (Required): A unique ID for the protocol.

GENUS SPECIES (Required): For example: Homo sapiens; Mus musculus
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: For example: Homo sapiens; Mus musculus
ORGAN PART: The term organ part is very broadly defined here. For example: bone marrow; islet of Langerhans
ORGAN PART ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: For example: bone marrow; islet of Langerhans
KNOWN DISEASE(S): Enter normal if no known diseases. For example: type 2 diabetes mellitus; normal
KNOWN DISEASE(S) ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY: For example: type 2 diabetes mellitus; normal
TIME OF COLLECTION: Enter the time in date-time format: yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ssZ. Supplying partial date is allowed. For example: 2016-01-21T00:00:00Z; 2016-03
COLLECTION PROTOCOL ID (Required): Protocol ID should have no spaces.
